The paper deals with inverse problems and regularization techniques, which are common topics in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of decomposable norms and linear operators also suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper discusses uniqueness and stability results, which are relevant to signal processing (cs.SI).
